The paper deals with the theoretical understanding of the Reeb space and its discrete approximations, which are commonly used in topological data analysis and visualization. This suggests that the paper may belong to the computer science sub-categories related to computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computer vision (cs.CV), and machine learning (cs.LG). Among these, cs.CG and cs.DS are the most likely categories as they are directly related to the mathematical and computational aspects of topological data analysis.
